quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  74,18,"He thought and determined."
  74,19,"May he perish{1}—how he determined!",footnotes:1:Literally ‘May he be killed’.
  74,20,"Again: may he perish—how he determined!"
  74,21,"Then he looked,"
  74,22,"then he frowned and scowled,"
  74,23,"then he retreated and acted arrogantly"
  74,24,"and said, “This is nothing but sorcery from the past."
  74,25,"This is nothing but the word of a human being.”"
  74,26,"I will roast him in Saqar{1}.",footnotes:1:Saqaris one of the names used for the fire of Hell.
  74,27,"But what can make you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>realize what Saqar is?"
  74,28,"It neither leaves nor spares;"
  74,29,"it scorches the flesh;"
  74,30,"over it are nineteen."
  74,31,"And We have not appointed except angels to be wardens of the Fire and have made their number nothing but a means of trial for the deniers—so that those given the Scripture may attain certitude, and those who have attained belief may increase in faith, and those given the Scripture and the believers may not doubt, and so that those in whose hearts is sickness and the deniers may say, “What did Allah desire by this parable?” Thus Allah misguides whomever He wills and guides whomever He wills, and none knows the soldiers of your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord except He, and this is nothing but a reminder to human beings."
  74,32,"But no! By the moon."
  74,33,"By the night as it retreated."
  74,34,"By the morning when it lights up—"
  74,35,"indeed, it is one of the greatest things:"
  74,36,"a warning to human beings,"
  74,37,"to whomever of you who wishes to advance or regress."
  74,38,"Every single self is held in pledge for what it has earned,"
  74,39,"except for those on the Right—"
  74,40,"in Gardens<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>, inquiring"
  74,41,"about the criminals:"
  74,42,"“What drove you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>into Saqar?”"
  74,43,"They said, “We were not of those who prayed,"
  74,44,"nor did we feed the destitute<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>,"
  74,45,"and we used to indulge<i class=""s"">(in falsehood) </i>with those who indulged,"
  74,46,"and we used to deny the Day of Recompense,"
  74,47,"until the certitude<i class=""s"">(of death) </i>came to us.”"
